<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<?import java.lang.*?>
<?import java.util.*?>
<?import javafx.scene.*?>
<?import javafx.scene.control.*?>
<?import javafx.scene.layout.*?>

<?import javafx.scene.text.Text?>
<?import javafx.scene.text.TextFlow?>
<BorderPane xmlns="http://javafx.com/javafx"
            xmlns:fx="http://javafx.com/fxml"
            fx:controller="Controller"
            prefHeight="400.0" prefWidth="400.0" styleClass="mainCont">
    <center>
        <VBox fx:id="ContentPop" styleClass="contentPop">
            <Label text="How To Play" styleClass="labelInst"/>
            <TextFlow styleClass="instText">
                <Text>
                    Hangman is a very simple game. It consists of you guessing a word from a specific
                    category. You will only get the amount of letter the word has and you will have to guess letter by letter
                    what this word is. If you get a letter wrong you will get a strike (start building the figure) and you
                    only get 6 strikes.
                </Text>
                <Text>
                    If you guess the word right you clear the category and can move on to the next.
                    once you clear all categories you win the game.You get 3 attempts on guessing the word in each
                    category. If you use up all of your attempts and still haven't guessed the word the game is over.
                </Text>

            </TextFlow>



        </VBox>
    </center>


</BorderPane>
